    "narrative": "The Zurich Zebras enter May 3rd with a clear focal point in **Pete Crow-Armstrong** (82.12), whose profile is optimized perfectly for today\u2019s slate. Facing a favorable matchup against a pitcher with a 4.72 xERA and a notably slow delivery, **Pete Crow-Armstrong** is a mandatory start; the combination of a high-ceiling park, wind blowing out, and his elite stolen base potential against a battery prone to surrendering steals provides the highest efficiency score in the lineup. **Junior Caminero** (75.13) follows as a secondary pillar of the offense, benefiting from a robust 15% skill boost against an exploitable arm and a prime #2 hole promotion. While **Yordan Alvarez** faces a tougher left-on-left dynamic, his elite 0.430 xwOBA keeps him firmly in the 63.70 range, ensuring he remains a start despite the sub-optimal platoon split.\n\nThe most difficult bench decision involved **Jerar Encarnacion**, whose score of 41.96 just barely missed the threshold. While he offers a helpful platoon advantage, his projection was suppressed by a lower base floor and a poor park factor, ultimately leading the optimizer to prioritize the higher-ceiling daily efficiency of players like **Carson Benge** (60.77). We are currently managing the absences of **Christian Yelich** and **Lars Nootbaar** on the IL, placing additional pressure on our utility depth. Managers should note that **Hyeseong Kim** carries a slight risk today; while his score of 55.99 reflects the favorable wind, he faces an \"elite hold\" catcher whose ability to suppress stolen bases may mitigate his primary path to value. With **Trea Turner** (67.99) leading off against a sub-par arm, we are positioned to compete heavily in the SB category, provided our high-speed outfielders capitalize on their favorable conditions.",
